main event: Sighting of two unidentified flying objects in Big Springs, Texas on August 12, 1965
interesting points: The objects were observed for 5 minutes and 10 seconds by civilian witnesses
One object was stationary, while the other was moving at approximately 30 seconds and 45 seconds
The report concludes that the objects did not have the characteristics of a satellite and were similar to meteors
The witnesses were instructed not to be contacted during the investigation, as they were assured their identities would be protected
The report includes technical details and measurements about the sighting, such as elevation and timings
